<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>The execute() method in Zend_Db_Adapter_Mysqli assumes that all statements return a result set, and therefore arrays need to be initialized to receive rows fetched from the result set.  This is not appropriate for statements like INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE, CREATE, etc.</p>

<p>Please set up result set arrays in this method only if the statement will return a result set.</p>

